{{infobox Chinese|l=Yin Water Snake|kanji=癸巳|romaji=mizunoto mi|onyomi=kishi|p=guǐsì|w=kuei-ssu|mi=kʷeɪ̯²¹ sɨ|y=gwai2 si6|j=gwai2 si6|ci=kʷɐi siː|mc=kjwɨj si|oc-bs=kʷeʔ si}}
{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}
'''Yin Water Snake also known as <!--please transliterate all the hiragana readings into romaji and provide the kanji--> Mizunotomi''' (癸巳) is one element of the {{ill|Sexagenary Cycle Comprehensive|ja|Sexagenary Cycle Comprehensive}}.

It is the 30th combination in the Sexagenary Cycle Comprehensive, preceded by {{ill|Renchen|ja|壬辰}} and followed by {{ill|Kougo|ja|甲午}}. In {{ill|Yin-Yang Five Elements Theory|ja|陰陽五行思想|lt=Yin-Yang Five Elements|lt_ja=陰陽五行}}, the {{ill|Gui|ja|癸|1=Mizunoto (癸)}} of the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}} represents yin water, while the {{ill|Snake|ja|巳}} of the {{ill|Twelve Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}} represents yin fire, and according to the principle of {{ill|Five Elements Theory: Mutual Destruction|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|lt=Mutual Destruction|lt_ja=相剋}} (water overcomes fire).

==Year of Mizunotomi==
A year in the {{ill|Common Era|ja|西暦}} that yields a remainder of 33 when divided by 60 is considered a Mizunotomi {{ill|year|ja|年}}.
