It is the 30th combination in the Sexagenary Cycle Comprehensive, preceded by {{ill|Renchen|ja|壬辰|12=draft|12=draft}} and followed by {{ill|Kougo|ja|甲午|12=draft|12=draft}}. In {{ill|Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|ja|陰陽五行思想|lt=Yin-Yang Five Elements|lt_ja=陰陽五行|12=draft|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Gui|ja|癸|1=Mizunoto (癸)|12=draft|12=draft}} of the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yin water, while the {{ill|Snake|ja|巳|1=Snake (zodiac)|lt=Snake (巳)|12=draft|12=draft}} of the {{ill|Twelve Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yin fire, and according to the principle of {{ill|Five Elements Theory: Mutual Destruction|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|lt=Mutual Destruction|lt_ja=相剋|12=draft|12=draft}} (water overcomes fire).

