{{infobox Chinese|l=Yin Water Snake|kanji=癸巳|romaji=mizunoto mi|onyomi=kishi|p=guǐsì|w=kuei-ssu|mi=kʷeɪ̯²¹ sɨ|y=gwai2 si6|j=gwai2 si6|ci=kʷɐi siː|mc=kjwɨj si|oc-bs=kʷeʔ si}}
{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}
'''Yin Water Snake also known as  Mizunotomi''' (癸巳) is one element of the {{ill|Sexagenary Cycle Comprehensive|ja|Sexagenary Cycle Comprehensive|12=draft|12=draft}}.

It is the 30th combination in the Sexagenary Cycle Comprehensive, preceded by {{ill|Renchen|ja|壬辰|12=draft|12=draft}} and followed by {{ill|Kougo|ja|甲午|12=draft|12=draft}}. In {{ill|Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|ja|陰陽五行思想|lt=Yin-Yang Five Elements|lt_ja=陰陽五行|12=draft|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Gui|ja|癸|1=Mizunoto (癸)|12=draft|12=draft}} of the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yin water, while the {{ill|Snake|ja|巳|1=Snake (zodiac)|lt=Snake (巳)|12=draft|12=draft}} of the {{ill|Twelve Earthly Branches|1=Earthly Branches|lt=Twelve Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yin fire, and according to the principle of {{ill|Five Elements Theory: Mutual Destruction|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|lt=Mutual Destruction|lt_ja=相剋|12=draft|12=draft}} (water overcomes fire).

==Year of Mizunotomi==
A year in the {{ill|Common Era|ja|西暦|1=Common Era|2=ja|3=西暦|4=zh|5=公元|6=es|7=Era común|8=nl|9=Gangbare jaartelling|10=simple|11=Common Era|12=draft|12=draft}} that yields a remainder of 33 when divided by 60 is considered a Mizunotomi {{ill|year|ja|年|12=draft|12=draft}}.
